✅ Basic Required Functionality (Base Grade)

The following required features were fully implemented:

Add a new Character

User is prompted for character details (Name, Health, Attack, Experience).

Character is persisted to the database using EF Core.

Edit an existing Character

User can update Health, Attack, Experience, and Name.

Changes are saved back to the database.

Display all Characters

All characters are listed with key attributes and current room location.

Search for a Character by Name

Case-insensitive search using LINQ.

Matching characters are displayed in a formatted table.

Logging

All major user actions (add, edit, display, search) are logged using ILogger.

Console and file logging are enabled.

🟡 C-Level Features Implemented (405/500)

The following C-level enhancements were added:

Abilities System (Foundation)

Characters can have abilities associated with them.

Ability display functionality is scaffolded and connected to the character model.

Ability execution pipeline is integrated with the game engine.

Combat System

Characters have a base Attack stat.

Attacking a monster subtracts health from the monster.

Monsters are removed from the database when defeated.

Combat output is rendered dynamically in Exploration Mode.

Character Abilities Display

Ability counts are displayed in inventory and stats.

System is structured for future ability damage modifiers.

🟢 B-Level Features Implemented (445/500)

The following B-level features were successfully completed:

Room System

Rooms include names, descriptions, coordinates, and directional exits.

Rooms are connected using North, South, East, and West navigation.

Rooms are persisted and retrieved using EF Core relationships.

Room Navigation

Player can move between connected rooms during Exploration Mode.

Movement validates exits and prevents invalid navigation.

Room transitions update the player’s location in the database.

Exploration Mode (Maze-Style Gameplay)

Player can explore the world visually using a compact map UI.

Current room details and inhabitants are displayed.

Available actions dynamically change based on room state.

Admin / Developer Mode

Separate Admin mode allows full CRUD access to game data.

Users can switch between Admin Mode and Exploration Mode at runtime.

Designed to support testing, debugging, and data setup.